About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son pushes Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

Click to watch all the Weekly Reliv episodes: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSXTaG1fT0cQAArE7eMbgq1G5iSXJ7tZC

snippet.title: PAV BHAJI | Mumbai Special Street Food Recipe Cooking In Village | Butter Pav Bhaji Recipe
snippet.description: Today we cook Mumbai Special street food Pav Bhaji recipe, with our beloved grandpa. In this cooking video, you'll get a glimpse of our traditional way of preparing this popular Indian street food with fresh ingredients. From chopping vegetables to slow-cooking the Bhaji, you'll witness every step of the process as we bond and have fun together. So sit back, relax, and get ready to feast your eyes on this culinary adventure in the heart of the village. Don't forget to try this recipe at home, and let us know how it turns out!

Episode 3758: Car Ka Golmol
--------------------------------------------------------
Everyone has been waiting for the car delivery, so Babita Ji questions Jethalal about it. Since Jetha is hesitant to respond, everyone begins to question him repeatedly. Tapu Sena tries to stop Iyer as he becomes ecstatic in response to their surprise. People in Gokhuldham hear music band troops playing and a brand-new red automobile pulling up suddenly. Has the car actually shown up yet? Remain tuned!

snippet.title: ROAST OF THE SHARKS | SHARK TANK INDIA SEASON 2
snippet.description:
This roast was performed at the sets of Shark Tank India Season 2.
It was the last & final shoot day of the season & my writer friend Md Anas and I turned this script around on just 48 hours of notice.  
I had a great time roasting the sharks and I would like to thank all of them for being such sports & Sony India for letting me do this. 
Drop in a like if you liked the video. Let me know in the comments which joke you liked the best. Share it with your friends and subscribe to my channel.

snippet.title: Ladakh tests World's First Mountain Top Lifi Laser¬†5G¬†internet | Sonam Wangchuk
snippet.description:
In this video, we explore the groundbreaking technology that is being tested in Ladakh - the world's first mountain-top LiFi laser 5G internet. Despite the harsh winter conditions, this technology has been successfully tested for two consecutive winters, bringing high-speed internet connectivity to the Secmol school. Join us as we delve into the details of this innovative technology and how it is transforming the way we connect with the world, even in the most challenging terrain


To make a pledge to heal the planet visit :  https://www.ilivesimply.org


All income from this YouTube channel goes to support projects in Ladakh... not to me or any individual.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

‡§¨‡•á‡§∏‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§¨‡•ç‡§ú‡•Ä, ‡§ï‡§Æ ‡§á‡§®‡•ç‡§ó‡•ç‡§∞‡•á‡§°‡§ø‡§Ø‡•á‡§®‡•ç‡§ü‡•ç‡§∏ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§´‡§ü‡§æ‡§´‡§ü ‡§¨‡§®‡§®‡•á ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä, ‡§¨‡•á‡§∏‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§¨‡•ç‡§ú‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ‡§è‡§Ç, cheela ki sabji kaise banate hain, No baking soda, cheela ki sabji kaise banaye,‡§¨‡•á‡§∏‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡§®‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§¨‡•ç‡§ú‡•Ä,
#besansabji #masalacurry #sabjirecipe #cheela 

Ingredients for
Besan Cheela Sabzi
‡§¨‡•á‡§∏‡§® - Gram flour - 1/2 cup (50 grams)
‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï - Salt - 1/4 tsp
‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï - Ginger - 1/4 tsp, grated
‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - Green chilli - 1/4 tsp, chopped
‡§π‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ - Coriander - 1 tsp
‡§§‡•á‡§≤ - Oil - 2 tbsp
‡§ú‡•Ä‡§∞‡§æ - Cumin - 1/2 tsp
‡§ü‡§Æ‡§æ‡§ü‡§∞ - Tomato - 1 piece (100 grams)
‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - Green chilli - 1 piece
‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï - Ginger - 1/2 inch
‡§π‡§≤‡•ç‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞ - Turmeric powder - 1/4 tsp
‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞ - Coriander powder - 1.5 tsp
‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç‡§ó - Asafoetida - 1 pinch
‡§ï‡§∂‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§≤‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - Kashmiri Red chilli - 1.5 tsp
‡§ï‡§∏‡•Ç‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡•á‡§•‡•Ä - Fenugreek leaves - 1 tbsp
‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä - Curd - 1/2 cup
‡§ò‡•Ä - Ghee - 1 tbsp
‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï - Salt - 3/4 tsp
‡§ó‡§∞‡§Æ ‡§Æ‡§∏‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ - Garam masala - 1/4 tsp  

How to make 

Making Cheela
In a mixing bowl, combine the gram flour, salt, grated ginger, chopped green chilli, and chopped coriander leaves.

Add water as required to make a smooth batter of pouring consistency. The batter should not be too thick or too thin. Mix well and keep it aside.

Heat a non-stick pan or tawa over medium heat. Grease it lightly with oil.

 Pour all the prepared batter onto the pan and spread it evenly in a circular motion to make a cheela. Cook for 2-3 minutes on low heat.

Drizzle oil around the edges and on top of the cheela. Flip the cheela and cook for another minute or until lightly browned. Remove from the pan and keep aside.

Making the Curry:
 Heat 2 tbsp oil in a pan over medium heat. Add 1/2 tsp cumin seeds and let them splutter.

Add paste of tomato, green chilli, and grated ginger. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes or until the tomatoes are soft and mushy.

Add 1/4 tsp turmeric powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder, 1 pinch of asafoetida, 1.5 tsp kashmiri red chilli powder, and 1 tbsp dried fenugreek leaves. Mix well and cook until the oil releases from the masala.

 Reduce the heat and add 1/2 cup whisked curd. Mix well and cook for 3-4 minutes or until the oil starts to separate from the mixture. Add 2 cups of water.

Add 1 tbsp ghee, 3/4 tsp salt (or to taste), and 1/4 tsp garam masala powder. Mix well and cook for another 1-2 minutes.

Cut the prepared cheelas into small pieces and add them to the curry. Mix well and cook for another 2-3 minutes over low heat.

Garnish with some fresh coriander leaves and serve hot with rice, roti or paratha.

‡§ó‡§∞‡§Æ ‡§Æ‡§∏‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ - Garam masala - 1/4 tsp  

How to make 

Making Cheela
In a mixing bowl, combine the gram flour, salt, grated ginger, chopped green chilli, and chopped coriander leaves.

Add water as required to make a smooth batter of pouring consistency. The batter should not be too thick or too thin. Mix well and keep it aside.

Heat a non-stick pan or tawa over medium heat. Grease it lightly with oil.

 Pour all the prepared batter onto the pan and spread it evenly in a circular motion to make a cheela. Cook for 2-3 minutes on low heat.

Drizzle oil around the edges and on top of the cheela. Flip the cheela and cook for another minute or until lightly browned. Remove from the pan and keep aside.

Making the Curry:
 Heat 2 tbsp oil in a pan over medium heat. Add 1/2 tsp cumin seeds and let them splutter.

Add paste of tomato, green chilli, and grated ginger. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes or until the tomatoes are soft and mushy.

Add 1/4 tsp turmeric powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder, 1 pinch of asafoetida, 1.5 tsp kashmiri red chilli powder, and 1 tbsp dried fenugreek leaves. Mix well and cook until the oil releases from the masala.

 Reduce the heat and add 1/2 cup whisked curd. Mix well and cook for 3-4 minutes or until the oil starts to separate from the mixture. Add 2 cups of water.

Add 1 tbsp ghee, 3/4 tsp salt (or to taste), and 1/4 tsp garam masala powder. Mix well and cook for another 1-2 minutes.

Cut the prepared cheelas into small pieces and add them to the curry. Mix well and cook for another 2-3 minutes over low heat.

Garnish with some fresh coriander leaves and serve hot with rice, roti or paratha.

#Ad
Hello guys, welcome back to my channel!
In today‚Äôs video, I am going to talk about Garnier Bright Complete Vitamin C Serum for face - a   miraculous product that helps rejuvenate dull skin, reveal radiant skin, and fade away pigmentation and dark spots.
Vitamin C as a skincare ingredient is best known for its skin-brightening capabilities. Since I was looking for effective solutions to reduce dark spots and dull skin, I thought of using this product and today, I'll be sharing the Garnier Vitamin C serum review.  
The vitamin C serum benefits are endless. To begin with, this antioxidant-rich vitamin C serum for face is enriched with Yuzu lemon that helps brighten your skin. Its advanced spot-reduction formula helps reduce acne and dark spots in a few days. What‚Äôs more! The non-oily, non-greasy texture of the serum blends easily into the skin without leaving any residue.
 
Now that you know what are the vitamin C serum uses and vitamin C serum benefits for face, let me show you all how to use vitamin C serum? First, cleanse your face. Then, pour a few drops of the serum on your palms and activate the product by rubbing it between your palms gently. Now, apply the vitamin C serum for face using mild tapping motions.
 
The Garnier Bright Complete Vitamin C Serum for face comes in beautiful packaging and travel-friendly size. The dropper available in the bottle makes the application easier and ensures no product is wasted. So, if you too are struggling with dark spots and dull skin, you won‚Äôt regret trying the Garnier Bright Complete Vitamin C Serum.  
 
Hope you guys liked my review on the Garnier Bright Complete Vitamin C Serum for face and found this video helpful. Don‚Äôt forget to share your review and let me know your thoughts in the comments section below.
 
For more such videos, do like, share, and subscribe to my channel. See you all in my next video! Till then, bye!

Tere Bin Episode 39 Teaser - 27th April 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Taarak and Jethalal are struck in thoughts as they were unable to reveal the truth to everyone till now. snippet.title: Interview with the cast of Ponniyin Selvan 2 | Anupama Chopra | Film Companion
snippet.description:
Anupama Chopra speaks with the cast of Ponniyin Selvan 2, the highly anticipated film directed by Mani Ratnam. In this interview, Vikram, Karthi, Jayam Ravi, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Trisha, Aishwarya Lekshmi, and Sobhita Dhulipala share their thoughts on various topics, including Mani Ratnam's vision for Ponniyin Selvan, the differences between the book and the film, and how the story has impacted their lives. The cast also discusses whether there are any particular aspects of the second part of this epic saga that audiences might miss. Don't miss this insightful conversation with the talented cast of Ponniyin Selvan 2!

Welcome to my channel one and all. The idea of this channel is to share content from all over the world in Telugu and this endeavor seems to be getting some traction. I want to mix travel videos, along with daily lifestyle vlogs and other kinds of content as well.

I have been to 186 countries so far and on a mission to visit every single nation on the face of this planet, Here is a brief introduction as more people discover my profile.

A detailed review of Akhil Akkineni‚Äôs latest flick Agent. Agent is a visual spy thriller with great production values directed by Surendar Reddy of Saira fame. snippet.title: The Flash - Official Trailer 2
snippet.description:
Watch worlds collide in trailer 2 for The Flash - Only in Theaters June 16. #TheFlashMovie 

Warner Bros. Pictures presents ‚ÄúThe Flash,‚Äù directed by Andy Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù). Ezra Miller reprises their role as Barry Allen in the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first-ever standalone feature film.

Worlds collide in ‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù when Barry uses his superpowers to travel back in time in order to change the events of the past. But when his attempt to save his family inadvertently alters the future, Barry becomes trapped in a reality in which General Zod has returned, threatening annihilation, and there are no Super Heroes to turn to. That is, unless Barry can coax a very different Batman out of retirement and rescue an imprisoned Kryptonian‚Ä¶ albeit not the one he‚Äôs looking for. Ultimately, to save the world that he is in and return to the future that he knows, Barry‚Äôs only hope is to race for his life. But will making the ultimate sacrifice be enough to reset the universe? 

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù ensemble also includes rising star Sasha Calle, Michael Shannon (‚ÄúBullet Train,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman v Superman: Dawn of Justice‚Äù), Ron Livingston (‚ÄúLoudermilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù), Maribel Verd√∫ (‚ÄúElite,‚Äù ‚ÄúY tu mam√° tambi√©n‚Äù), Kiersey Clemons (‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúSweetheart‚Äù), Antje Traue (‚ÄúKing of Ravens,‚Äù ‚ÄúMan of Steel‚Äù) and Michael Keaton (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman‚Äù).

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù is produced by Barbara Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù) and Michael Disco (‚ÄúRampage,‚Äù ‚ÄúSan Andreas‚Äù). The screenplay is by Christina Hodson (‚ÄúBirds of Prey,‚Äù ‚ÄúBumblebee‚Äù), with a screen story by John Francis Daley & Jonathan Goldstein (‚ÄúDungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming‚Äù) and Joby Harold (‚ÄúTransformers: Rise of the Beasts,‚Äù ‚ÄúArmy of the Dead‚Äù), based on characters from DC. The executive producers are Toby Emmerich, Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Marianne Jenkins.

Joining director Muschietti behind the camera are director of photography Henry Braham (‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), production designer Paul Denham Austerberry (‚ÄúIT Chapter Two,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Shape of Water‚Äù), editors Jason Ballantine (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Great Gatsby‚Äù) and Paul Machliss (‚ÄúThe Gentlemen,‚Äù ‚ÄúBaby Driver‚Äù), and costume designer Alexandra Byrne (‚ÄúDoctor Strange,‚Äù ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù); the score is by Benjamin Wallfisch (‚ÄúThe Invisible Man,‚Äù the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films).

Warner Bros. Pictures presents a Double Dream/a Disco Factory production of an Andy Muschietti film, ‚ÄúThe Flash.‚Äù It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and is set to open in theaters in North America on June 16, 2023 and internationally beginning 14 June 2023.

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù ensemble also includes rising star Sasha Calle, Michael Shannon (‚ÄúBullet Train,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman v Superman: Dawn of Justice‚Äù), Ron Livingston (‚ÄúLoudermilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù), Maribel Verd√∫ (‚ÄúElite,‚Äù ‚ÄúY tu mam√° tambi√©n‚Äù), Kiersey Clemons (‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúSweetheart‚Äù), Antje Traue (‚ÄúKing of Ravens,‚Äù ‚ÄúMan of Steel‚Äù) and Michael Keaton (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman‚Äù).

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù is produced by Barbara Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù) and Michael Disco (‚ÄúRampage,‚Äù ‚ÄúSan Andreas‚Äù). The screenplay is by Christina Hodson (‚ÄúBirds of Prey,‚Äù ‚ÄúBumblebee‚Äù), with a screen story by John Francis Daley & Jonathan Goldstein (‚ÄúDungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming‚Äù) and Joby Harold (‚ÄúTransformers: Rise of the Beasts,‚Äù ‚ÄúArmy of the Dead‚Äù), based on characters from DC. The executive producers are Toby Emmerich, Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Marianne Jenkins.

Joining director Muschietti behind the camera are director of photography Henry Braham (‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), production designer Paul Denham Austerberry (‚ÄúIT Chapter Two,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Shape of Water‚Äù), editors Jason Ballantine (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Great Gatsby‚Äù) and Paul Machliss (‚ÄúThe Gentlemen,‚Äù ‚ÄúBaby Driver‚Äù), and costume designer Alexandra Byrne (‚ÄúDoctor Strange,‚Äù ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù); the score is by Benjamin Wallfisch (‚ÄúThe Invisible Man,‚Äù the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films).

Warner Bros. Pictures presents a Double Dream/a Disco Factory production of an Andy Muschietti film, ‚ÄúThe Flash.‚Äù It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and is set to open in theaters in North America on June 16, 2023 and internationally beginning 14 June 2023.

snippet.title: NEW! Ep 3757 - Babitaji Ki Gaadi Ka Celebration?! | Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah | ‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï ‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ
snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu 

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu 

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Lyrics : 

Chhori thi phulan bargi 
Dil tod ke mera dhar gi
Ja jee le apni zindagi
Mere naam ki ib tu marr gi
Raatan ne kare phone thi
Mitthi si teri tone thi
Ek dum tu itna badli
Sochun wa chhori koun thi
Dekhi kise aur ke gelya
Baatan ne fer gayi tu
Meri nazran te khud ne
Usse din ger gayi tu
Nazran te nazar mili na
Bheetar mein chor thha tere
Meri bas tu ae thhi re 
Tanne the or bhatere

Tanne to pyaar ae na tha
Mera bhi moh tha ghatt gya
Dimag mein nafrat bhargi
Dil yu tere pe datt gya
Yaadan m jindgi katt jya
Jeene ki chah bhi ghat jya
Teri gelyan mel mile na
Kah ke koi pachhe hat jya
Titlian brge yaar likhe
Kade likh deyi mastaani re
Meri peed likhe to khuda manu
Bta likh dega ke jaani re
Mere hathan mein lakeer na teri
Dil mein tasveer se teri
Daru mein ghol ke peeu
Deyi har peed re teri

Chaati ke laa maa meri
Nyu boli thi mere te 
Bhul jya addi usne
Khel gayi jo tere te 
Baba bhi keh gya chele
kyu ba nke pagal jee rya
wa teri thi ae konya 
Jis khatir daru pee rya
Peena meri aadat na
Jazbaat pilawe to pee lyu
Tanne y mein ruswai mein
Teri yaad stawe to pee lyu
Yo madi h yo achhi h
teri fikar pilawe to pee lyu
Manne bera Jeete jee tu na milni
Yo umar ghatawe to pee lyu

Beshak ghunghat ke parde mein
Manne dekhan aaiye marde na
Main Arthi te bhi uthh jyunga
Je dil pe hath tu dharde ne
Yaad thhi phulan bargi
Bheetar m sari sad gyi
Mehndi la aur kise ki
Zindagi mein aage badh gayi
zayada main mangu konya
Itna sa kaam tu kar de
Bade chore ka tere
Naam mere naam pe dhar de
Rah le jis gelya rehna 
Manne to dard yo Sahna
Yaar jo nya banaya
Bas uste yo ye kehna
Bas uste yo ye kehna
Bas uste yo ye kehna

Bichne ka ghana shonk hai usne 
Tu Dil jiske pairan main bichhaye fire hai
Re mera jhutha ishq hai wo 
Tu jisne muh pe laaye feere hai
Tu jisne muh pe laaye feere hai
